  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Since rkt 1.13, more specifically https://github.com/coreos/rkt/pull/2983, it is possible to run pods with security opt-outs, a.k.a. _privileged_ pods, using the new `--insecure-options={capabilities,paths,seccomp,all-run}` command-line parameters.\n\nCurrently, Kubelet sets all caps to rkt containers when `v1.SecurityContext.Privileged` is used. Instead, the kubelet should use `--insecure-options=all-run`.\n\nUntil https://github.com/coreos/rkt/issues/2996 is implemented, it is a per-pod option rather than per-app one, we might have to decide to pass it when every containers in the pod have `v1.SecurityContext.Privileged` (or use an annotation...).\n",
